abstract: >-
  Prompt as a Process (PaaP) is a framework for treating Markdown SOPs as
  deployable applications, runnable end-to-end by sufficiently reliable
  language models. This repository formalizes the framework via 20
  architectural principles, a scoring rubric, an empirical survey of
  community skills, four documented evaluations of a meta-skill that
  generates other skills, and a runnable example. Intended for practitioners
  authoring or evaluating LLM workflow files (e.g., SKILL.md), and
  researchers studying the post-orchestration-framework ecosystem.
